en_182700_0	Former Central Bank Governor Arjuna Mahendran, Perpetual Treasuries owner Arjun Aloysius and PLT CEO Kasun Palisena have been named as suspects in the Central Bank Bond scam case.
en_182700_1	Colombo Fort Magistrate Lanka Jayaratne gave the order this morning (Feb. 02).
en_182700_2	The Magistrate also directed Arjuna Mahendran who is now in Singapore to arrive in Sri Lanka and give a statement to Criminal Investigation Department before 15th of this month.
en_182700_3	Meanwhile, yesterday the Colombo High Court extended the freeze of 24 bank accounts owned by PTL and its subsidiaries.
